annotationA: Nicotinamide mononucleotide adenylyltransferase (Nmnat) is an essential enzyme in the NAD salvage pathway, catalyzing the last step of NAD synthesis. Nmnat is also a neuronal maintenance factor that protects neurons from excitotoxicity, environmental stress and protein misfolding induced degeneration
annotationB: NAD kinase 2, mitochondrial; Mitochondrial NAD(+) kinase that phosphorylates NAD(+) to yield NADP(+). Can use both ATP or inorganic polyphosphate as the phosphoryl donor
